Title: ESTIMATING THE SOLVABILITY OF PATTERN CLASSIFICATION PROBLEMS  
Author: S. HARING J.N. KOK and M.A. VIERGEVER 
Address: P.O. Box 80089, 3508 TB Utrecht, The Netherlands  
Affiliation: 1 Department of Computer Science, Utrecht University  Department of Computer Science, Leiden University 3 Image Center Utrecht, Utrecht University Hospital  
Abstract: Training of feed-forward networks is sensitive for learning-parameters, network architecture, etc. So if a feed-forward network fails to solve a pattern classification problem one never knows if the cause of the failure is in the network or in the problem itself. Hence a well-founded indication of the problem's solvability is a helpful tool in engineering with feed-forward networks. We present a method to estimate the solvability of a pattern classification problem. The method is based on the estimation of the Bayes error-rate of the problem, and intergrates classical theories into a novel application. The proposed algorithm is tested on a number of benchmarks and proved to be reliable. We argue that the approach is feasible if many patterns are available and if the dimension of the patterns is relatively low.
