Reference-contexts: Without knowledge of a well-founded estimate of a minimum error-rate, one hardly knows whether further fine-tuning of the algorithm would eventually yield better results. The theoretical bound on the error-rate of a pattern classification problem is called the Bayes error-rate <ref> (Duda and Hart 1973) </ref>. In this paper we propose a method to estimate the Bayes error-rate of a pattern classification problem; the method is straightforward and combines algorithms that have been known for decades to a novel application.
