Reference-contexts: In this paper we propose a method to estimate the Bayes error-rate of a pattern classification problem; the method is straightforward and combines algorithms that have been known for decades to a novel application. First we use Parzen window estimation <ref> (Parzen 1962) </ref> to make estimates of the probability density functions that underly the data. To calculate the Bayes error-rate we need to integrate these functions; for that we apply Monte Carlo integration (Press, Teukolsky, Vetterling, and Flannery 1988). The algorithm is very convenient and almost independent of parameters.
